sql:
SELECT max_delay
FROM flight_performance
WHERE performance_id = 1;

SELECT period_name
FROM flight_periods
ORDER BY period_name ASC;

SELECT period_name
FROM flight_periods
WHERE duration_days = 15;

SELECT period_name 
FROM flight_periods 
ORDER BY period_name;

SELECT AVG(average_delay) AS avg_delay
FROM flight_performance
WHERE period_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Average delay refers to the mean delay time in minutes for flights that were delayed.; 
- Top routes are determined based on the highest average delay times across all periods.; 
- Access patterns may indicate user interest or need for specific flight performance data.; 
- The detailed performance metrics can be used to identify trends or problematic areas in flight operations and access usage.
